                  <interp inst="t18270215-254-crimeloc1362" type="placeName" value="Turk's-row, Chelsea"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270215-254-crimeloc1362" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270215-254-off1360 t18270215-254-crimeloc1362"></join>. These boots lay on a box by the fire-place - I met the prisoner (who is a stranger) in Jews'-row, between eleven and twelve o'clock, on the 15th - we got into conversation; she said she could help me to two or three days' work every week, and she would go home with me, that she might know where to send for me; we went into my room; and as I turned my back to bid a neighbour good bye, she must have concealed the boots; she went away - I went out, and returned at half-past seven o'clock; I then missed them - I am sure they were there when she was in the room - nobody else was there - I locked my door when I went out, and found it still locked - I never allowed her to take them.</p>
